[SN]TITLE[SN]
Builder cleared of trench manslaughter

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A builder has been cleared of killing his brother-in-law.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Adi Andrews, 46, was found at the bottom of a 13ft (4m) trench in Wormbridge, Herefordshire, on 22 October 2012.
Philip Parry, 51, had denied manslaughter, but pleaded guilty to breaches of health and safety regulations.
Mr Justice Popplewell directed the jury at Birmingham Crown Court to find Parry not guilty of manslaughter.
Parry, from Preston-on-Wye in Herefordshire, has been sentenced to 12 months in prison, suspended for two years after admitting failing to discharge his duties as an employer.
He was also given a curfew for four months and told to complete 100 hours of unpaid work.
Parry and his brother-in-law had been doing building work at the bottom of a trench on Whitfield Estate.
